## MODULE 1: SETS AND POWER SETS

### Key Concepts & Real-World Examples
* **UNION (A ∪ B):** Combining all items. 
* **INTERSECTION (A ∩ B):** Only the overlapping items. 
* **POWER SET P(A):** The set of all possible subsets. Formula: 2ⁿ elements.
  * *Everyday Analogy:* A pizza place offers 3 toppings: {Pepperoni, Onion, Mushroom}. The Power Set is every possible pizza you could order. You could get nothing (cheese pizza), just Pepperoni, Pepperoni + Onion, or all three. 2³ = 8 possible combinations.

