## MODULE 3: FUNCTIONS

### Key Concepts & Real-World Examples
Functions map a starting group (Set X) to a destination (Set Y).
* **INJECTIVE (One-to-One - "No Sharing"):** Every X maps to a completely unique Y. 
  * *Everyday Analogy:* A movie theater. Every person gets their own unique seat. Nobody is sitting on top of each other. (Empty seats left over are fine).
* **SURJECTIVE (Onto - "Full Coverage"):** Every single Y is mapped to by at least one X. 
  * *Everyday Analogy:* A hotel on New Year's Eve. Every single room in the building is booked. No room is empty. (Friends sharing a room is fine).
* **BIJECTIVE (Both):** A perfect 1:1 pairing.
  * *Everyday Analogy:* The final round of Musical Chairs. 5 kids, 5 chairs. No sharing, and no empty chairs.

