## MODULE 4: ALGEBRAIC STRUCTURES

### Key Concepts & Real-World Examples
* **GROUPS (With Identity and Inverse):** A set with an operation that allows you to undo actions.
  * *Everyday Analogy:* A steering wheel. If you turn the wheel 90 degrees to the right (Action), the Identity is the wheel resting exactly in the center (0 degrees). The Inverse is turning the wheel 90 degrees to the left to undo your action and get back to the center.
* **LATTICES:** A hierarchy where items have unique upper and lower bounds.
  * *Everyday Analogy:* A corporate organizational chart. The "Greatest Element" is the CEO at the very top who oversees everything. The "Minimal Element" is the entry-level interns at the bottom. 

